RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 18540. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 26 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEKNOWSTHEDRILL prompted the pace two wide under nice rating and to the outside of RAVENEL, applied more pressure leaving the far turn, poked a head in front after six furlongs, responded when asked nearing the lane and spurted clear of threats, opened up under right handed asks in mid stretch and proved clearly best while remaining on her left lead. CONGRESS HALL , three wide between rivals early, was rated back a bit near the five eighths, angled out and ranged up four wide to loom past the five sixteenths, saw the winner get away from her in upper stretch but kept on willingly to be clearly second best. BEATUBYACHUBINOSE broke a step slow, was used four wide to contention, tracked three wide into the far turn, took closer order past the five sixteenths, chased into the lane then faded in the final eighth. LOVE IS STRONG , fractious in the gate, came away in good order then was rated back off the leaders heading into the first turn, drafted further back mid way through the backstretch run, angled out but lacked a solid response. RAVENEL took over into the first turn and secured the inside, set a slow but pressured pace, ceded the lead past the five sixteenths, raced two wide into the lane and weakened. SHEMADEMELUCKY , two wide stalking early, dropped in, failed to kick on past the three eighths and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 24335. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $8,000, allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRANSFER THE FUNDS settled well back off of a hotly contested early pace, angled out around the final turn, circled rivals six wide into the stretch, leveled off under asking past the three sixteenths, sustained while laying in a few times and got up in the final jumps. GRAND MANNER disputed the pace to the inside of DEJOHN through solid opening fractions, shook clear heading to the far turn then had to brace for an outside challenge from NO ME DIGAS, kept that one at bay into the lane then opened up under a drive while on his left lead, wandered outward with a sixteenth remaining and got over to his correct lead, kept on valiantly but just could not fend off the winner's charge. NO ME DIGAS , perched three wide off the embattled leaders, edged up and gave hard chase of GRAND MANNER from the three eighths, saw that one get away in upper stretch, kept on grinding, cut back into the margin between foes in deep stretch but was out finished. TRIPLE TITOS , off the duel while saving ground, remained inside into the stretch, made progress along the rail near the sixteenth marker then flattened out. GOD IS LOVE broke a step slow, settled outside a rival, angled out and chased four wide between foes into the lane but lacked a finishing response. BODE LYNX , well placed saving ground, gained some under a ride heading to the five sixteenths, angled out into the stretch, lacked a further punch past the three sixteenths and faded. DEJOHN got into a battle outside GRAND MANNER around the first turn, carried that scrum to about the half mile marker, failed to go on leaving the far turn and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 101. Allowance Purse 77650. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Claiming Since December 26 Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BACKNTHEWOODS , six deep contesting the early pace, dropped in a few paths leaving the far turn with a short lead outside STEINBECK, shook clear mid turn under some coaxing, kept on under left handed asks inside the furlong grounds and held firm with good energy through the wire. JOHN THE BEAR , four wide between runners disputing the early pace, bumped with a foe and rated back a touch near the turn, advanced four wide to loom into the lane, gave hard chase from there and dug in gamely to preserve the place. KARAN'S NOTION , hard sent and battled inside five others through the opening furlong, was shuffled back into the turn, trailed saving ground mid turn, angled out and came back gamely between runners. HOPEFUL TREASURE rated off the embattled leaders early, edged up three wide past the five sixteenths, angled out for the drive and churned on. KADRI , with the early pace between foes, bumped with JOHN THE BEAR nearing the turn, came back on between runners nearing the lane, gave hard chase in mid stretch and faded late. WAR TOCSIN , five wide between horses and vying early, was lightly steadied nearing the turn, circled five to six wide into the stretch but came up empty. STEINBECK , two wide between foes battling early on, inherited the rail leaving the far turn and stayed on to spar inside the winner, failed to keep pace nearing mid stretch and faded. An objection by the rider of KADRI against JOHN THE BEAR for alleged interference nearing the turn was not allowed. An objection by the rider of JOHN THE BEAR against the winner for alleged interference approaching the turn was not allowed.
